item.title: Arcanists
item.dc:creator: @slavemaster veer
item.description:
@slavemaster wrote:

Well, would you look at you! Aren’t you just something spectacular? You wrote a few lines of code for a “parameter parser”, a small parser that uses regular expressions to parse a subset of HTML4. It’s not like there are open-source parsers that can fully parse HTML, XHTML, hell even XML in general which are probably faster, easier to use, and more elegant than anything you could have come up with.

It’s not that anyone is envious of what code you probably leeched to extract applet parameters out of a FunOrb game client page, because frankly they aren’t difficult to write, and most people probably don’t waste their time writing external UIs to load the applet when browsers do the job just fine. Your code is probably nothing special but likely nobody would care as much if you didn’t for some odd reason add “anti-leech” to your code. Anybody who leeches your code is somebody you should be happy took the time to actually use your code, considering it is a mere implementation of the approach people have been using for ages.

[code]... document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); document.write(' '); ...[/code]
[code][/code] Was that /really/ so hard? Get over yourself.

@03data: All the code archives are easily available on the FunOrb servers, so is there really any point to dumping them all?
